DataElement.preferredName: Diagnosis Performed Observation Outcome Data Null Type Reason ISO21090.ST.v1.0
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The identification of a disease or illness by examining the signs and symptoms. The text and/or code that describes why no result was provided. EXAMPLE(S): (1) Subject refused to answer question. (2) Error message returned by equipment to explain why the device was unable to produce a result.

DataElementConcept.preferredName: Diagnosis Performed Observation Outcome Data Null Type Reason
DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: The investigation, analysis and recognition of the presence and nature of disease, condition, or injury from expressed signs and symptoms; also, the scientific determination of any kind; the concise results of such an investigation.:Executed and carried through to completion.:Watching something and taking note of what happens.:The result of an action._A collection or single item of factual information, derived from measurement or research, from which conclusions may be drawn.:A special value that may be stored in some database columns to represent an unknown, missing, not applicable, or undefined value.:Something distinguishable as an identifiable class based on common qualities.:An explanation of the cause of some phenomenon or action.
